obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12336)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12336&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Seamen's Provident Fund Act, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise expressly provided, the provisions of this Act shall apply to every seaman and to`
  line `the employer of such seaman.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12337)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 29 of 1997, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12337&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "agreement with the crew" means the agreement referred to in section 100 or, as the case may`
  line `be, section 114 of the Merchant Shipping Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Board of Trustees of the Seamen's Provident Fund constituted under`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) "continuous discharge certificate" means the certificate referred to in section 99 of the`
  line `Merchant Shipping Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "contribution" means a contribution payable in respect of a member under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(e) "employer", in relation to a seaman, means the owner of the ship on which the seaman is`
  line `employed or engaged, or the agent of such owner or the master of the ship;`
  line
  line `(f) "Fund" means the Seamen's Provident Fund established under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(g) "Government" means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) "master" and "ship" have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Merchant`
  line `Shipping Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "member" means a seaman who is in possession of a continuous discharge certificate and who`
  line `is admitted as a member of the Fund;`
  line
  line `(j) "Merchant Shipping Act" means the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(k) "Scheme" means the Seamens Provident Fund Scheme framed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(l) "seaman" means a person employed or engaged as a member of the crew of a ship under the`
  line `Merchant Shipping Act but does not include ^1`
  line `[a welfare officer, nurse, musician, pilot or deck`
  line barber];
  line
  line `(m) "service" means the period of employment of a seaman under the agreement with the crew`
  line `and includes any period in respect of which wages are paid or are payable to him;`
  line
  line `(n) "wages" means the basic wages for the time being payable to a seaman under the agreement`
  line `with the crew and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any remuneration to which he is entitled in respect of holidays or any leave period;`
  line
  line `(ii) any increase of such wages in accordance with such agreement or any other agreement`
  line `between the parties;`
  line
  line `but does not include the overtime allowance.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12338)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Seamen's Provident Fund Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12338&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, frame a scheme to be called the Seamen's Provident Fund Scheme for the establishment`
  line `of a provident fund for seamen and there shall be established, as soon as may be after the framing of the`
  line `Scheme, a Fund in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Scheme may provide for all or any of the matters`
  line `specified in the Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Scheme may provide that any of its provisions shall take effect either prospectively or`
  line `retrospectively on such date as may be specified in this behalf in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) The Scheme shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in`
  line `force other than this Act or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to, amend, vary or rescind the`
  line Scheme.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12339)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Vesting of Fund, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12339&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Fund referred to in sub-section (1) of section 3 shall vest in, and be`
  line `administered by, the Board constituted under section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The moneys in the Fund shall be applied for--`
  line
  line `(a) meeting the pay and allowances of the employees of the Board and other administrative`
  line `expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All moneys in the Fund shall be deposited in ^1`
  line `[an approved bank] or be invested in such securities`
  line `as may be approved by the Government.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Explanation. --In this section, "approved bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or a subsidiary bank as defined in clause (k)`
  line `of section 2 of the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act,1959 (38 of 1959), or a corresponding new`
  line `bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1997, s. 3, for "the State Bank of India" (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  line
  line `2. Explanation added by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12340)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Board of Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12340&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, a Board to be known`
  line `as the Board of Trustees of the Seamen's Provident Fund which shall be a body corporate having`
  line `perpetual succession and a common seal and may, by that name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Board shall be in Bombay or at such other place as the Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Government;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than three persons appointed by the Government from amongst its officials;`
  line
  line `(c) three persons representing employers, to be appointed by the Government after consultation`
  line `with such organisation or organisations of employers as may be recognised by the Government in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `(d) three persons representing seamen, to be appointed by the Government after consultation with`
  line `such organisation or organisations of seamen as may be recognised by the Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms and conditions subject to which a member of the Board may be appointed and the time,`
  line `place and procedure of the meetings of the Board, including the quorum, shall be such as may be`
  line `provided for in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall administer the Fund vested in it in such manner as may be specified in the`
  line Scheme.
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall perform such other functions as it may be required to perform by or under any`
  line `provision of the Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12341)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Committees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12341&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, from time to time, constitute one or more committee or`
  line `committees for exercising any power or discharging any duty of the Board or for inquiring into, or`
  line `reporting and advising on, any matter which the Board may refer to such committee or committees.`
  line
  line `(2) A committee may include persons who are not members of the Board but their number shall not`
  line `exceed one-half of its strength.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12342)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of employees of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12342&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government shall appoint a Seamens Provident`
  line `Fund Commissioner who shall be the chief executive officer of the Board and shall be subject to the`
  line `general control and superintendence of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may also appoint as many Deputy Seamen's Provident Fund Commissioners ^1`
  line `***, as it may consider necessary, to assist the Seamen's Provident Fund Commissioner in the discharge`
  line `of his duties.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may appoint such other officers and employees as it may consider necessary for the`
  line `efficient administration of the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) No appointment to the post of the Seamen's Provident Fund Commissioner or Deputy Seamen's`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner ^2`
  line `*** shall be made except after consultation with the Union Public Service`
  line `Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation shall be necessary in regard to any such appointment--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period not exceeding one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person to be appointed is at the time of his appointment--`
  line
  line `(i) a member of the Indian Administrative Service; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the service of the Government in a Class I or Class II post or in the service of the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(5) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `the Seamen's Provident Fund Commissioner and of the officers referred to in sub-section (2) shall be such`
  line `as may be specified by the Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `other officers and employees of the Board shall be such as may be specified by the Board with the`
  line `approval of the Government.`
  line
  line `(7) All persons appointed under this section shall be the employees of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and other officers whose maximum monthly salary is not less than six hundred rupees" omitted`
  line `by Act 29 of 1997, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  line `2. The words "or to any other post carrying a maximum monthly salary of not less than six hundred rupees" omitted`
  line `by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12343)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Contributions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "and thereafter at the rate of eight per cent." (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12343&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employer to whom this Act applies shall, in respect of each seaman`
  line `(being a member) employed by him, contribute to the Fund for the period beginning with the 1st day of`
  line `July, 1964 and ending with the 31st day of March, 1968, at the rate of six per cent.,`
  line ^1
  line `[for the period`
  line `beginning with the 1st day of April, 1968 and ending with the 31st day of December, 1977, at the rate of`
  line `eight per cent. and thereafter at the rate of ten per cent. or such higher rate as may be specified in the`
  line `Scheme] of the wages paid or payable to each such seaman and every such seaman shall also contribute to`
  line `the Fund an amount equal to the contribution payable by the employer in respect of him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of contribution aforesaid shall, in so far as it relates to the period prior to the`
  line `commencement of the Scheme, be payable by the employer or, as the case may be, by the seaman only on`
  line `such date (being a date not earlier than sixty days after the commencement of the Scheme) as the`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The employer shall pay, in respect of each seaman (being a member) employed by him, both the`
  line `employer's contribution and the employees contribution and shall be entitled to recover from the seaman`
  line `the employee's contribution by deduction from his wages and not otherwise.`
  line
  line `(3) Every employer shall also pay such sums of money as may be specified in the Scheme towards the`
  line `cost of administering the Fund.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the amount of any contribution under sub-section (1) or any sum payable under`
  line `sub-section (3) contains a part of a rupee, then, if such part if fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to`
  line `one complete rupee and if such part is less than fifty paise it shall be ignored.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12344)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Determination of moneys due from employers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12344&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Seamen's Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner or any Deputy Seamen's Provident Fund Commissioner may, by order, determine the`
  line `amount due from any employer under any provision of this Act or of the Scheme and for this purpose`
  line `may conduct such inquiry as he may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer conducting the inquiry under sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of such inquiry,`
  line `have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for`
  line `trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line span@
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person or examining him on oath;`
  line
  line span@
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line span@
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line
  line span@
  line `(d) issuing commission for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `and any such inquiry shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and`
  line `228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) No order shall be made under this section unless the employer has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of representing his case.`
  line
  line `(4) An order made under this section shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12345)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Mode of recovery of moneys due from employers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12345&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any amount due from an employer in`
  line `respect of any contribution payable to the Fund, or damages recoverable under section 18 or any charges`
  line `payable by him under any other provision of this Act or under any provision of the Scheme, may, if the`
  line `amount is in arrear, be recovered by the Government in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12346)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Fund deemed to be recognised Provident Fund under Act 43 of 1961.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12346&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `the Income-tax Act, 1961, the Fund shall be deemed to be a recognised provident fund within the`
  line `meaning of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12347)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Protection against attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12347&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount standing to the credit of any member in the`
  line `Fund shall not in any way be capable of being assigned or charged and shall not be liable to attachment`
  line `under any decree or order of any court in respect of any debt or liability incurred by the member, and`
  line `neither the official assignee appointed under the Presidency Towns Insolvency Act, 1909 (3 of 1909), nor`
  line `any receiver appointed under the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), shall be entitled to, or have`
  line `any claim on, any such amount.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount standing to the credit of any member in the Fund at the time of his death and payable`
  line `under the Scheme to his nominee shall, subject to any deduction authorised by the Scheme, vest in the`
  line `nominee and shall be free from any debt or other liability incurred by the deceased or the nominee before`
  line `the death of the member.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12348)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Priority of payment of contributions over other debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12348&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where any employer is adjudicated`
  line `insolvent, or, being a company, an order for winding up is made, the amount due from the employer`
  line `in respect of any contribution payable to the Fund, damages recoverable under section 18 or any charges`
  line `payable by him under any other provision of this Act or under any provision of the Scheme shall,`
  line `where the liability therefor has accrued before the order of adjudication or winding up is made, be`
  line `deemed to be included among the debts which under section 49 of the Presidency Towns Insolvency`
  line `Act, 1909 (3 of 1909), or under section 61 of the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), or under`
  line `section 530 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), are to be paid in priority to all other debts in the`
  line `distribution of the property of the insolvent or the assets of the company being wound up, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12349)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Employer not to reduce wages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12349&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No employer shall, by reason only of his liability for the`
  line `payment of any contribution to the Fund or any charges under this Act or the Scheme, reduce, whether`
  line `directly or indirectly, the wages of any seaman to whom the Scheme applies or the total quantum of`
  line `benefits in the nature of old age pension, gratuity or provident fund to which the seaman is entitled under`
  line `the agreement with the crew or any other agreement between the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12350)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Inspectors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 1997, s. 6, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12350&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint such`
  line `employees of the Board, as the Government thinks fit, to be Inspectors for the purposes of this Act and`
  line `the Scheme, and may define their jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Inspector appointed under sub-section (1) may, for the purpose of inquiring into the`
  line `correctness of any information furnished in connection with this Act or the Scheme or for the purpose of`
  line `ascertaining whether any of the provisions of this Act or of the Scheme have been complied with--`
  line
  line `(a) require an employer to furnish such information as he may consider necessary in relation to`
  line `the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) at any reasonable time and with such assistance, if any, as he may think fit, enter any office or`
  line `board any ship, search the same and require any one found in charge thereof to produce before him`
  line `for examination any accounts, books, registers and other documents in relation to the employment of`
  line `seamen or the payment of wages to seamen;`
  line
  line `(c) examine, with respect to any matter relevant to any of the purposes aforesaid, the employer,`
  line `his agent or servant or any other person found in charge of the office or the ship or whom the`
  line `Inspector has reasonable cause to believe to be, or to have been, an employee in the office or on the`
  line ship;
  line
  line `(d) make copies of, or take extracts from, any book, register or other document maintained in`
  line `connection with the Fund and, where he has reason to believe that any offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by an employer, seize with such assistance as he may think fit such book, register or`
  line `other document or portions thereof as he may consider relevant in respect of that offence;`
  line
  line `(e) exercise such other powers as the Scheme may provide.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to any search or seizure under sub-section (2) as they apply to any search or seizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code.]`
  line
  line `(4) Every Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12351)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 12-11-1998).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12351&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, for the purpose of avoiding any payment to be made by himself under`
  line `this Act or under the Scheme or of enabling any other person to avoid such payment, knowingly makes or`
  line `causes to be made any false statement or false representation shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ^1`
  line `[one year, or with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees], or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(2) The Scheme may provide that any person who contravenes, or makes default in complying with`
  line `any of the provisions thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes or makes default in complying with any provision of this Act shall, if no`
  line `other penalty is elsewhere provided by or under this Act for such contravention or non-compliance, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act or under the Scheme`
  line `except on a report in writing of the facts constituting such offence made by the Seamen's Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner or by an Inspector appointed under sub-section (1) of section 15, with the previous`
  line `sanction of such authority as may be specified in this behalf by the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12352)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12352&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act or the Scheme`
  line `is a company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act or the`
  line `Scheme has been committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence was committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any offence under this Act or the Scheme is committed by a company not registered in`
  line `India and such a company has an agent in India which agent is also a company, then the provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply to such agent as if the offence was committed by that agent.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm and other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12353)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to recover damages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12353&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where any employer makes default in the payment of`
  line `any contribution to the Fund or in the payment of any charges payable under any other provision of this`
  line `Act or under the Scheme, the Government may recover from the employer such damages, not exceeding`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of the amount of arrears, as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12354)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Transfer of account`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=12354&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where a seaman leaves the seafaring profession with no present intention`
  line `of resuming that profession and obtains employment in any establishment to which the Employees'`
  line `Provident Funds Act, 1952 (19 of 1952), applies, the amount standing to the credit of such seaman in the`
  line `Fund shall be transferred, within such time as may be specified by the Board in this behalf, to the credit of`
  line `his account in the provident fund of that establishment, if the seaman so desires and the rules in relation to`
  line `that provident fund permit such transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (29170)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=29170&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by order in writing, exempt any seaman to whom this`
  line `Act applies and his employer from the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act if, in the`
  line `opinion of the Board, the seaman is in enjoyment of benefits in the nature of provident fund or pension`
  line `and such benefits, separately or jointly are on the whole not less favourable to the seaman than the`
  line `benefits provided by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an exemption has been granted under sub-section (1), the employer shall not at any time`
  line `after the grant of the exemption, without the leave of the Board, reduce the total quantum of benefits in`
  line `the nature of provident fund, pension or gratuity to which the seaman was entitled at the time of grant of`
  line `such exemption.`
  line
  line `(3) Any exemption granted under this section may be cancelled by the Board, by order in writing, if`
  line `the employer fails to comply with the requirements of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the employer has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the proposed cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (29171)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Protection for acts done in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=29171&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Government or the Board or any officer or employee thereof in respect of anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or under the Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (29172)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=29172&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by order, direct that any power or duty which by this Act`
  line `or by the Scheme is conferred or imposed upon the Government (other than the power to frame a scheme`
  line `under section 3) shall, in such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the`
  line `direction, be exercised or discharged also by such officer or authority as may be so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, with the prior approval of the Government, delegate to its Chairman or to any of`
  line `its employees, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as it may specify, such of its functions`
  line `under this Act as it may deem necessary for the efficient administration of the Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (29173)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=29173&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Government may make such order or give such direction, not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or expedient for the removal of the difficulty, and any such order`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (29174)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Scheme to be laid before Houses of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985&sectionId=29174&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00013_196604_1517807320985
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any Scheme framed under this Act shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is framed, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions, and, if before`
  line `the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in any provision of the Scheme or both Houses agree that any provision in the`
  line `Scheme should not be made, that provision of the Scheme shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `नाविक भविष्‍य-निधि अधिनियम,1966`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/1633/3/H1966-4.pdf`
  sourceKind pdf
  fetchedAt `2026-05-10T09:48:04.852Z`
